        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-green-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">✓ Pro Tip</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">QI and ZA are the two highest-scoring two-letter words. Playing QI on a triple-letter square scores <span class="text-white font-medium">33 points</span> from just two tiles. Master all 20 of these and you'll never be stuck unable to play parallel.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Category 2: Q-Without-U Arsenal (15 Words)</h2>
      <p>Drawing the Q without a U is no longer a disaster once you memorize these. Every word here is valid in SOWPODS and several also work in TWL. The Q tile is worth 10 points — these words let you deploy it instead of exchanging it.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">QI — 11 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Life force in Chinese philosophy. The single most important Q-word.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">QOPH — 18 pts</p>
